{{死刑}}
'''炮决'''是一种[[死刑|处决]]方法，受刑者通常被绑在[[加农炮|加农炮]]口，然后被炮弹打死。乔治·卡特·斯滕特（George Carter Stent）描述的过程如下：<ref name="#1">''Havholm'' (2008), [https://books.google.com/books?id=vxuSORJ-Tv8C&pg=PA77 p. 77] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vxuSORJ-Tv8C&pg=PA77 |date=20200903231613 }}</ref>[[File:Vereshchagin-Blowing_from_Guns_in_British_India.jpg|右]]创作于1884年的油画《{{Le|英国人镇压印度人起义|Suppression of the Indian Revolt by the English}}》，描绘了英国人炮决叛乱者的场景。这起事件发生在1872年1月15日的[[旁遮普邦|旁遮普邦]][[马莱尔科特拉|马莱尔科特拉]]，65名锡克和平主义组织的成员被军方炮决。注：这幅画据说被英国王室买下并可能已经被销毁。（目前下落不明）]]{{Quote|text=囚犯通常被绑在炮上，被炮口抵着后腰的上边。开炮后，只见他的头直冲上天飞了四五十英尺；上肢飞向天上，落到四处，也许有一百码那么远；下肢落在炮口下；躯干全被轰碎，看不出一点痕迹。}}
据传[[莫卧儿帝国|莫卧儿帝国]]早在16世纪就开始使用炮决，直到20世纪。16世纪和17世纪，最早在1509年，[[葡萄牙帝國|葡萄牙殖民者]]跨越他们的帝国，从[[锡兰|锡兰]]（今[[斯里兰卡|斯里兰卡]]）到[[莫桑比克|莫桑比克]]再到[[巴西|巴西]]都使用了这种处决方式。<ref name="auto">''Calcutta Review'' (1851), [https://books.google.com/books?id=mYdHAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA395 p. 395] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mYdHAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA395 |date=20201023175559 }}</ref><ref name="auto1">''Alden'' (1996), [https://books.google.com/books?id=7nVIBhrRb9AC&pg=PA55 p. 55] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7nVIBhrRb9AC&pg=PA55 |date=20200916084104 }}</ref><ref>''Southey'' (1822), [https://books.google.com/books?id=h4AiAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA469 p.469] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=h4AiAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA469 |date=20200807102712 }}</ref>[[莫卧儿帝国|莫卧儿人]]在整个17世纪至18世纪都实施过炮决，特别是对反叛分子。<ref>17th century case, ''Afsos, Court'' (1871), [https://books.google.com/books?id=a-BRAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA64 p. 64] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a-BRAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA64 |date=20200719234937 }}, 18th century case ''Hazārah, McChesney, Khorrami'' (2012), [https://books.google.com/books?id=8tLE4hjSyjEC&pg=PA54 p. 54] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8tLE4hjSyjEC&pg=PA54 |date=20200806112811 }}</ref>

炮决与[[英属印度|英属印度]]殖民政府关系最为密切。在[[印度民族起义|印度民族起义]]后，炮决被英国人用来处决叛军和那些被判逃兵罪的土著人。<ref>''Long'' (1869), [https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR397#v=onepage&q=blown&f=false p. 397–398] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR397#v=onepage&q=blown&f=false |date=20200801220417 }}</ref><ref>'''February 1781''' ''Parlby'' (1822), [https://books.google.com/books?id=-d0KAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA188 p. 188] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-d0KAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA188 |date=20201106170737 }}, '''May 1783''' ''Baillie'' (1788), [https://books.google.com/books?id=3SIUAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA490 p. 490] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3SIUAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA490 |date=20200810100717 }}, '''July 1783''' ''Forbes'' (1815), [https://books.google.com/books?id=82AOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA123 p. 123] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=82AOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA123 |date=20200918224835 }}, '''October 1783''' ''Forbes'' (1815), [https://books.google.com/books?id=82AOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA133 p. 133] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=82AOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA133 |date=20200807025824 }} '''November 1783'''  ''Baillie'' (1788), [https://books.google.com/books?id=3SIUAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA468 p. 468] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3SIUAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA468 |date=20200719061700 }}</ref>18世纪后半叶，英国人开始使用这种[[莫卧儿王朝|莫卧儿王朝]]使用过的方式。<ref>Long (1869), [https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR51 p. 51] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR51 |date=20200724212204 }} [https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR224 page 224] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR224 |date=20200818160310 }}</ref>

在[[印度次大陆|印度次大陆]]，炮决作为一种处决方式有着特殊的宗教作用。其使囚犯不能留全尸，还将遗骸四处散布，所以它有效地阻止了[[印度教|印度教徒]]必要的葬礼。<ref>Past Present, Volume 233, Issue 1, November 2016, Pages 185-225, Calculated to Strike Terror: The Amritsar Massacre and the Spectacle of Colonial Violence by Kim A. Wagner, https://academic.oup.com/past/article/233/1/185/2915150/Calculated-to-Strike-Terror-The-Amritsar-Massacre {{Wayback|url=https://academic.oup.com/past/article/233/1/185/2915150/Calculated-to-Strike-Terror-The-Amritsar-Massacre |date=20171012165849 }}</ref>因此对信徒而言，这种刑罚超越了死亡。外国侵略者对此很了解，因此炮决通常没有被同期的外国侵略者在非洲，大洋洲或美洲采用。最近的一次炮决发生在1930年的[[阿富汗王國|阿富汗]]，11名[[潘傑希爾省|潘杰希尔]]（Panjshiri）叛乱分子被罕见地施行炮决。<ref name="auto2">''Cullather, Meyerowitz'' (2003), [https://books.google.com/books?id=V5NdS-k7FUMC&pg=PA50 p. 50] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=V5NdS-k7FUMC&pg=PA50 |date=20200807102717 }}</ref>

== 方式 ==
一种常见的炮决方式是将人绑在炮口前射杀。据传偶尔会使用真正的实心圆弹，但被证实更常见的是[[空包弹|空包弹]]或[[葡萄彈|霰弹]]。以下将罪犯绑起来的描述发生在1839年7月7日对[[多斯特·穆罕默德汗|多斯特·穆罕默德汗]]的战役中，由{{Le|舒贾沙阿|Shah Shujah Durrani}}下令：<ref name="#1"/>

{{Quote|text=那三个人被用绳子绑在了炮上，背部抵着炮口。绳子的一头被系紧在一边的车轮辐条上，绕紧手臂并打了个结，再穿过炮口绕紧另一只手臂，最后系紧在另一边的车轮辐条上，使他们不能动弹。}}

虽然在开炮之前将受刑者固定在炮口是迄今为止报道最多的方法，但1596年[[伊斯坦布尔|伊斯坦布尔]]的一次案例声称受刑者实际上是被塞进炮管里被处决的。<ref>''Boyar, Fleet'' (2010), [https://books.google.com/books?id=hHd2OizxNCcC&pg=PA112 p. 112] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hHd2OizxNCcC&pg=PA112 |date=20200812145257 }}</ref>现有的报告证实，偶尔有人被绑在火箭弹上，在空中爆炸。据说这是[[海德尔·阿里|海德尔·阿里]]统治时期（1761-1782年）对[[婆罗门|婆罗门]]的惩罚，也是1800年[[马拉塔帝国|马拉塔帝国]]一起叛国案中的惩罚。<ref>''Campbell'' (1839), [https://books.google.com/books?id=PHgOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA421 p. 421] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PHgOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA421 |date=20201103042616 }}</ref><ref>''Duff'' (1826, 3), [https://books.google.com/books?id=_7A5AQAAIAAJ&pg=PA190 p. 190] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_7A5AQAAIAAJ&pg=PA190 |date=20200727213142 }}, and ''Lal, Prinsep'' (1831), [https://books.google.com/books?id=OH5CAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA127 p. 127] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OH5CAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA127 |date=20200824042854 }}</ref>
== 存在的问题 ==
施行炮决时可能会发生意外。1857年，在[[菲奥兹普尔|菲奥兹普尔]]的一次大规模处决中，按照命令是使用空包弹，但是有些炮却装上了霰弹。大炮对面的一些观众被霰弹击中，导致有些人不得不截肢。此外，一些士兵没有撤退到安全地带，遭飞溅的肉块和骨头击中而受伤。<ref name="#1"/>在另一个案例中，一名即将被炮决的士兵成功在炮声响起前溜倒，结果如下：<ref>''American Peace Society'' (1858) [https://books.google.com/books?id=EMYBAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA23 p. 23] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EMYBAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA23 |date=20200728073101 }}</ref> 

{{Quote|text=一个不幸的家伙刚好在炮响前滑脱了将他绑在炮上的绳子，他的上肢几乎烧了起来。正当他遭受痛苦时，一位中士用一把手枪对准他的头开了三枪，每枪都使他一阵畏缩。最终他被用步枪从头后面开枪，血从鼻子和嘴喷涌而出，就像水泵里涌出的水一样。这是最可怕的场面。我见过各种死法，但没有比他更惨的。}}

其他令人不寒而栗的记载提到[[猛禽|猛禽]]在行刑场上空盘旋，俯冲下来捕食飞到空中的人肉碎片。还有狗在刑场附近徘徊，并冲到现场狼吞虎咽地吃掉行刑后撒得到处都是的“美味”。<ref>"It is a curious fact, and well attested by many persons present, that a number of [[Kite_(bird)|kites]] (a bird of prey very common in India) actually accompanied the melancholy party in their progress to the place of execution, as if they knew what was going on, and then kept hovering over the guns from which the culprits were to be blown away, flapping their wings, and shrieking, as if in anticipation of their bloody feast, till the fatal flash, which scattered the fragments of bodies in the air; when, pouncing on their prey, they positively caught in their talons many pieces of the quivering flesh before they could reach the ground! At sight of this the native troops employed on this duty, together with the crowd which had assembled to witness the execution, set up a yell of horror".. The description is from the execution of those found guilty in the Vellore Mutiny in 1806, ''Blakiston'' (1829), [https://books.google.com/books?id=wboRAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA309 p. 309] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wboRAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA309 |date=20200726031027 }}.</ref><ref>In an 1845 [[Herat|Herat]] case: "It was a scene that I shall never forget—a horrid spectacle, and touched me to the very heart. The broken limbs of the unfortunate man were scattered in all directions, while his bowels, which had not been thrown to so great a distance, were in an instant devoured by the dogs that were loitering about the spot." ''Ferrier'' (1856), [https://books.google.com/books?id=eT4cLqALvtMC&pg=PA189 p. 189] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eT4cLqALvtMC&pg=PA189 |date=20200807131302 }}.</ref>

== 莫卧儿帝国 ==
在[[印度次大陆|印度次大陆]]，炮决有着悠久而多样的历史，18世纪中期以来的许多报告都证明了这种方式的多种用途。炮决在叛乱期间被用作各种罪行的惩罚。在这里，重点讲莫卧儿的炮决传统，比英国在同一次大陆的使用要早。

一些历史学家指出，炮决在印度次大陆是一种“古老的莫卧儿式惩罚”。<ref>See, for example, ''Heathcote'' (1995), [https://books.google.com/books?id=YSK8AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA105 p. 105] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YSK8AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA105 |date=20200718181224 }}, and ''Fremont-Barnes'' (2007), [https://books.google.com/books?id=DVoNNeKsKmgC&pg=PA79 p. 79]{{Dead link|date=January 2017 |bot=medic }}.</ref>据传就在第一位莫卧儿皇帝[[巴布尔|巴布尔]]统治之前，他的儿子[[胡马雍|胡马雍]]在1526年3月6日与[[洛迪王朝|洛迪王朝]]的一次冲突中炮决了100名阿富汗战俘。<ref>''Sabahuddin, Shukla'' (2003), [https://books.google.com/books?id=FW4WqqLVzLEC&pg=PA122 p. 122] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FW4WqqLVzLEC&pg=PA122 |date=20200718220745 }}</ref>在17世纪后半叶，印度北部的[[賈特人|贾特人]]起来反抗莫卧儿帝国，据传[[奥朗则布|奥朗则布]]皇帝下令将他们的一个头目炮决。<ref>''Afsos'' (1871), [https://books.google.com/books?id=a-BRAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA64 p. 64] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a-BRAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA64 |date=20200719234937 }}</ref>据传Purbeel Singh是Oomga镇（靠近今[[比哈尔邦|比哈尔邦]]的奥郎加巴德市）最后一位长官，他被一位不知名的莫卧儿皇帝带到西边14英里的一个镇上炮决。<ref>''Asiatic Soicety of Bengal'' (1847), [https://books.google.com/books?id=iAfgAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA658 p. 658] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iAfgAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA658 |date=20200720073116 }}</ref>1716年，锡克叛军[[班達·辛格·巴哈都爾|班达·辛格·巴哈都尔]]被皇帝[[法鲁克锡亚|法鲁克锡亚]]击败，在他被处决后，他的儿子被下令“用大炮炸碎”。<ref>''Hazārah, McChesney, Khorrami'' (2012), [https://books.google.com/books?id=8tLE4hjSyjEC&pg=PA54 p. 54] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8tLE4hjSyjEC&pg=PA54 |date=20200806112811 }}</ref>

前面的案例是炮决反叛分子或敌军，但莫卧儿时代也有一些将这种处决方式用于其他类型犯罪的例子。例如，在[[贾汉吉尔|贾汉吉尔]]时代（1605-1627年）的一件传闻轶事中，皇帝将6位[[毛拉|毛拉]]炮决，原因是他们同意或批准了绑架一个印度教女孩并让她嫁给一名穆斯林军官。<ref>''Bakshi'' (1997), [https://books.google.com/books?id=7O3dD1N93hUC&pg=PA103 p. 103–104] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7O3dD1N93hUC&pg=PA103 |date=20201023175631 }}</ref>在1714年，盗窃事件让行军部队很头疼，于是他们设计了一个陷阱。两个小偷被隐蔽的卫兵抓住，后来被炮决。在1719年的一次围攻中，莫卧儿军队的逃兵问题被解决，因为指挥官当着军队的面将4名逃兵炮决。<ref>''Irvine'' (1922), thieves, [https://archive.org/stream/latermughals01irviuoft#page/286/mode/2up p. 287], and deserters, [https://archive.org/stream/latermughals01irviuoft#page/414/mode/2up p. 415].</ref>

== 葡萄牙帝国 ==
[[葡萄牙帝国|葡萄牙殖民者]]被指在他们的多个殖民地使用炮决作为一种死刑方式。以下是一个简短的回顾：

=== 斯里兰卡 ===
据传在1509年左右，葡萄牙探险家[[弗朗西斯科·德·阿尔梅达|弗朗西斯科·德·阿尔梅达]]在[[锡兰|锡兰]]炮决了多人。<ref name="auto">''Calcutta Review'' (1851), [https://books.google.com/books?id=mYdHAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA395 p. 395]</ref>1656年荷兰围攻[[科伦坡|科伦坡]]期间，该城遭受了严重饥荒。一位在哺乳期的母亲因为饥饿而停止产奶，她的婴儿也濒临死亡。她选择杀死它，然后吃掉。当葡萄牙将军知晓她的食人行为，她被下令炮决。但在这种特殊的情况下，神职人员和主要市民对将军进行了劝阻，使她幸免于难。<ref>''Ribeiro, Le Grand'' (1847), [https://books.google.com/books?id=D6M2AAAAMAAJ&pg=PA138 p. 138] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=D6M2AAAAMAAJ&pg=PA138 |date=20200808142432 }}</ref>

=== 莫桑比克 ===
探险家{{Le|弗朗西斯科·巴雷托|Francisco Barreto}}在1569-1573年{{Le|莫诺莫塔帕|Kingdom of Mutapa}}的战役中一度囚禁过大约50名穆斯林，并让他们“被[[穿刺|刺穿]]，被炮决，被树干撕碎，被砍死或枪杀”。<ref name="auto1">''Alden'' (1996), [https://books.google.com/books?id=7nVIBhrRb9AC&pg=PA55 p. 55]</ref>据传在18世纪中叶[[葡屬東非|葡属东非]]西北部的[[太特|太特]]，对奴隶的死刑是炮决。在19世纪的前10年，据传一个劫匪头子被葡萄牙人抓住并被炮决。<ref>According to the same source, this punishment was only inflicted in cases of rebellion, otherwise, deportation was the most severe punishment ''Thoman'' (1869), [https://books.google.com/books?id=86xGAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA111 p. 111] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=86xGAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA111 |date=20201105155738 }}</ref><ref>''Salt'' (1814), [https://books.google.com/books?id=QzGKBkUTLrkC&pg=PA39 p. 39–40] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QzGKBkUTLrkC&pg=PA39 |date=20200831055115 }}</ref>

=== 巴西 ===
在1618年的巴西，当地人对葡萄牙人的抵抗毫不动摇，尽管他们的一位领袖阿马罗（Amaro）被俘虏并被炮决。<ref>''Southey'' (1822), [https://books.google.com/books?id=h4AiAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA469 p. 469] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=h4AiAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA469 |date=20200807102712 }}</ref>

== 英属印度 ==

=== 1857年以前 ===
英国人在[[印度民族起义|印度民族起义]]之前就有一项悠久的传统，就是炮决那些被判叛乱或逃兵罪的[[印度兵|印度兵]]。据一位历史学家的说法，这项传统始于1760年，当时政府审查了死刑的执行方式。在{{Le|佩尔加纳斯24区|24 Parganas}}，人们发现军事上常用的死刑方式是鞭打致死。政府将炮决视作一种古老的莫卧儿王朝的惩罚方式并采用了它，因为这种方式相对于用鞭子打死人来说更具威慑力，更公开，更人道。早在1761年，[[拉基普尔|拉基普尔]]镇就获令“用大炮射击被俘的盗贼头目以威慑其他人”。<ref>Long (1869), [https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR51 p. 51] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR51 |date=20200724212204 }} [https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR224 page 224] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR224 |date=20200818160310 }} for 17 November 1760 decision, footnote remarking that thief was a carpenter named Nayn</ref>从技术上讲，在[[军事法庭|军事法庭]]的案例中，似乎在1857年前法庭都是由本地官员而不是英国人组成的，但有补充说：“虽然他们被主管官员领导，然而主管官员的职责仅仅是转录证据，并向本地官员提供咨询和指导”。<ref>''Anderson'' (1859), [https://books.google.com/books?id=H2kJAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA39 p. 39] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H2kJAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA39 |date=20200807025830 }}</ref>

1764年3月，一位本地军官想要引诱他的部队到敌军那里去，他被军事法庭审判并当着部队的面被炮决。<ref>At that time, [[Shuja-ud-Daula|Shuja-ud-Daula]], who was defeated by the British in the Battle of Buxar some months later</ref><ref>''Broome'' (1850), [https://books.google.com/books?id=JcQDM10JmcgC&pg=PA435 p. 435] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JcQDM10JmcgC&pg=PA435 |date=20200724212202 }}</ref>同年9月，{{Le|赫克托尔·芒罗|Hector Munro, 8th laird of Novar}}少校处决了24或25名“罪魁祸首”，他们导致一个营的士兵逃走（逃走的原因是“缺乏回报”、”缺少粮食”以及气候和疾病问题）。一位评论者赞成处决，说：“从那以后，兵变的倾向就没有出现过。”1775年，印度士兵Muctoom Sahib（被英国人指定为“指挥官”）拒绝东印度公司外国雇佣军所下达乘船前往孟买的“命令”。受到指挥官的鼓舞并出于对他的尊重，Muctoom Sahib的手下也跟着做了。外国雇佣军将Muctoom Sahib炮决作为报复。他的手下丧失了士气，开始前往孟买。<ref>For 1764 and 1775 events, ''Butalia'' (1998), [https://books.google.com/books?id=eV262iNGUb4C&pg=PA273 p. 273] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eV262iNGUb4C&pg=PA273 |date=20200831055118 }}. Hector Munro's report on 24 executed to the House of Commons may be read here: ''Adolphus'' (1840), [https://books.google.com/books?id=FhEOAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA268 p. 268] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FhEOAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA268 |date=20200718181238 }}. In his letter dated 18 September to the [[East_India_Company|East India Company]], however, Monro says 25, detailing where they were sent for execution, ''Long'' (1869), [https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR397#v=onepage&q=blown&f=false p. 397–398] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QXwoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PR397#v=onepage&q=blown&f=false |date=20200801220417 }}.</ref>1782年，[[巴尔达曼|巴尔达曼]]和[[巴拉克普尔|巴拉克普尔]]爆发了兵变。3名叛乱者被巴尔达曼法庭判处死刑，其中两人被炮决，一人被[[绞刑|绞死]]。在[[巴拉克普尔|巴拉克普尔]]审判中，受审的5人中有4人被判处炮决，另一人被鞭打1000次，并“被用绳子勒着脖子从营地里赶出去”。<ref>''Deerrett'' (1783), [https://books.google.com/books?id=o5YrAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA83 p. 83–85] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o5YrAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA83 |date=20200727212011 }}</ref>在{{Le|第三次盎格鲁-迈索尔战争|Third Anglo-Mysore War}}期间（1789-1792年），6个团因拖欠军饷而叛变，并控制了他们的军官。秩序恢复后，两个最活跃的人被炮决。<ref>''Almon'' (1791), [https://books.google.com/books?id=0zTgAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA637 p. 637] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0zTgAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA637 |date=20201105155740 }}</ref>1781年和1783年发生的几起案例表明，除了叛乱者，逃兵也被处以炮决。<ref>'''February 1781''' ''Parlby'' (1822), [https://books.google.com/books?id=-d0KAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA188 p. 188] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-d0KAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA188 |date=20201106170737 }}, '''May 1783''' ''Baillie'' (1788), [https://books.google.com/books?id=3SIUAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA490 p. 490] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3SIUAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA490 |date=20200810100717 }}, '''July 1783''' ''Forbes'' (1815), [https://books.google.com/books?id=82AOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA123 p. 123] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=82AOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA123 |date=20200918224835 }}, '''October 1783''' ''Forbes'' (1815), [https://books.google.com/books?id=82AOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA133 p. 133] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=82AOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA133 |date=20200807025824 }}, '''November 1783'''  ''Baillie'' (1788), [https://books.google.com/books?id=3SIUAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA468 p. 468] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3SIUAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA468 |date=20200719061700 }}</ref>

不只有[[印度兵|印度兵]]被炮决。1798年，英军[[马德拉斯|马德拉斯]]第一炮兵营发生兵变，一名英国士兵被判处炮决。<ref>''Butalia'' (1998), [https://books.google.com/books?id=eV262iNGUb4C&pg=PA273 p. 273–274] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eV262iNGUb4C&pg=PA273 |date=20200831055118 }}</ref>然而，这似乎是例外。一位历史学家说，士兵福斯特（Forster）是唯一记录在案的被英国当局处以炮决的欧洲人。<ref>''Grey, Garrett'' (1996), [https://books.google.com/books?id=S8AN0-cO-RYC&pg=PA216 p. 216] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S8AN0-cO-RYC&pg=PA216 |date=20200812003444 }}. However, a case from 1784 in the [[cantonment|cantonment]] at [[Arcot|Arcot]] says that a mutiny over reduced pay broke out in October among European troops, and that one active serjeant was condemned to be blown from a gun. ''Baldwin'' (1785), [https://books.google.com/books?id=ixcAAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA390 p. 390] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ixcAAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA390 |date=20200728233213 }}.</ref>

1804年，在一次军事行动中，伯奇（Birch）中尉指挥的部队拒绝离开他们的营地。伯恩（Burn）上校认为有必要采取严厉措施，他召集了军事法庭，两名涉案军官被判炮决，另外九人遭到“严酷鞭打”。有人在完全赞同这一行为的情况下写道：”有充分理由相信这一措施产生了最佳效果，因为军团在随后的围攻中表现得最为坚定和得体”。<ref>''Philippart'' (1823), [https://books.google.com/books?id=e_I8zCCqhV4C&pg=PA497 p. 497] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=e_I8zCCqhV4C&pg=PA497 |date=20200907110558 }}</ref>

1806年的{{Le|韦洛尔兵变|Vellore mutiny}}以夜间对英国军官和士兵的屠杀开始，许多[[印度兵|印度兵]]被镇压杀死，6个人被判处炮决。<ref>''Rosselli'' (1974), [https://books.google.com/books?id=px6WdehjC-MC&pg=PA52 p. 52] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=px6WdehjC-MC&pg=PA52 |date=20200822163414 }}</ref>1812年，一个密谋杀害欧洲军官的阴谋在[[特拉凡哥尔|特拉凡哥尔]]被发现，两名主谋被炮决，其他一些人被处以绞刑。<ref>''Wilkes'' (1815), [https://books.google.com/books?id=mJw1IV-EAAoC&pg=PA310 p. 310] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mJw1IV-EAAoC&pg=PA310 |date=20200818160311 }}</ref>1819年，6名投奔被吞并的{{Le|那格浦尔王国|Nagpur kingdom}}被逐王公的逃兵被英国人逮捕，并于2月7日被炮决。<ref>''Macready'' (1853), [https://books.google.com/books?id=rPobAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA236 p. 236] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rPobAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA236 |date=20200818160308 }}</ref>1832年的[[班加罗尔|班加罗尔]]，一个声称要消灭所有欧洲人的阴谋被发现。在大约100名牵连者中，4人被判处炮决，另有2人被枪毙。<ref>Detailed report by captain Doveton from 1844, ''Doveton'' (1844), [https://books.google.com/books?id=CihGAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA620 p. 620–624] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CihGAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA620 |date=20201105204310 }}</ref>

有时，尽管一个人被判处死刑，但他仍可能有希望得到赦免或减刑。1784年，一个团因军饷不足而叛变。莱因（Laing）中将镇压了反叛，并下令将12人炮决。<ref>On achieved rank under Madras governor [[George_Macartney,_1st_Earl_Macartney|George Macartney]] ''Munro'' (1789), [https://books.google.com/books?id=Eg8NAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA344 p. 344] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Eg8NAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA344 |date=20200812003453 }}</ref>然而，12人中的最后1人非常幸运：他被绑在大炮口上，导火索烧毁了3次。然后他问莱因中将，他是否真的注定要这样死去，莱因中将决定赦免他。<ref>''Munro'' (1789), [https://books.google.com/books?id=Eg8NAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA358 p. 358] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Eg8NAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA358 |date=20201106170736 }}</ref>1795年，[[梅迪尼普尔|梅迪尼普尔]]军事法庭以叛乱罪判处5名印度兵炮决，另外3名士兵被处以绞刑。然而，他们的案件被上诉，判决被减刑为开除现役。<ref>''Seton-Karr'' (1865), [https://books.google.com/books?id=LdUMAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA181 p. 181–185] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LdUMAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA181 |date=20200806112813 }}</ref>在{{Le|1824年巴拉克普尔兵变|Barrackpore mutiny of 1824}}中，血腥镇压开始四天后，被派往[[第一次英缅战争|第一次英缅战争]]前线的印度兵感到不满，一位名叫Bindee Tiwarree的47团领导人伪装成一名[[法基爾|法基尔]]藏了起来。在随后军事法庭的审判中，他被判处炮决，但他却被用链子吊死。在他死后，尸体被吊在铁笼里示众长达几个月。<ref>''Wellington, Wellington'' (1868), [https://books.google.com/books?id=mx8yAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA332 p. 332] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mx8yAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA332 |date=20201030172549 }}, and ''Pogson'' (1833), [https://books.google.com/books?id=ikAIAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA30 p. 30–31] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ikAIAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA30 |date=20201103084122 }}</ref>1836年，一名叫Jemadar Rungish的印度兵因临阵脱逃并抛弃他的欧洲军官而被判有罪。他被判处炮决，但这一判决被减刑为“流放海外”。<ref>''Asiatic Journal'' (1837), [https://books.google.com/books?id=eSoLAQAAMAAJ&pg=RA1-PA58 p. 58] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eSoLAQAAMAAJ&pg=RA1-PA58 |date=20201030043438 }}</ref>

=== 大起义 ===
在1857年[[印度民族起义|印度民族起义]]中，炮决被英军广泛使用。《艾伦的印度邮件》（Allen's Indian Mail）的记载显示了英国人执行炮决的规模和频率：[[File:Blowing_Mutinous_Sepoys_From_the_Guns,_September_8,_1857_-_steel_engraving.jpg|缩略图]]{{Quote|text=6月8日，第35轻步兵团的两名印度兵被炮决。6月10日，在[[白沙瓦|白沙瓦]]的[[卢迪亚纳|卢迪亚纳]]，大约40名来自第54团的士兵被炮决。6月13日，驻扎在[[菲奥兹普尔|菲奥兹普尔]]的第45团的10名印度兵被炮决，2人被绞死。<ref>Number executed specified in "Government Records" (1911), [https://books.google.com/books?id=WiMeAQAAIAAJ&q=ferozepore+%22blown+from%22+45th&dq=ferozepore+%22blown+from%22+45th&hl=no&sa=X&ei=i4WPUb7_GcLI4ASpsoDIDA&ved=0CC8Q6AEwAA p. 132] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WiMeAQAAIAAJ&q=ferozepore+%22blown+from%22+45th&dq=ferozepore+%22blown+from%22+45th&hl=no&sa=X&ei=i4WPUb7_GcLI4ASpsoDIDA&ved=0CC8Q6AEwAA |date=20201106091235 }}</ref>同一天，在[[安巴拉|安巴拉]]，第54团的10名印度兵遭遇了同样的命运。同月26日，在[[奥郎加巴德|奥郎加巴德]]，1人被炮决，1人被绞死，3人被枪毙。7月8日，在[[傑赫勒姆|杰赫勒姆]]，被俘叛军被认为会被炮决。19日的[[奥郎加巴德|奥郎加巴德]]，一个被炮决，两人被枪毙。9月5日的塞塔拉（Settara），6人被炮决。9月17日的[[木爾坦|木尔坦]]，1人被炮决，121人被立即处死。9月23日，在[[卡拉奇|卡拉奇]]，1人被炮决，7人被绞死，20人被驱逐出境。（当地被军法审判的人数随后增加到4人被炮决，14人被绞死，22人被驱逐出境，3人被斩首。）在10月底[[阿格拉|阿格拉]]附近的{{Le|罗希尔坎德|Rohilkhand}}地区，有一人被炮决。11月16日的孟买，第10团的两名印度兵被炮决。<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=JrgOAAAAQAAJ ''Allen's Indian Mail''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JrgOAAAAQAAJ |date=20201106161743 }} (1857), pp. 465, 466, 502, 549, 601, 731, 771, 911</ref>}}
作为官方统计数据的例子，而不是报纸报道的集合，根据一份1859年提交给[[英国下议院|英国下议院]]的关于[[旁遮普地区|旁遮普地区]]的[[白沙瓦|白沙瓦]]河谷叛乱的文件，1857年5月至9月期间记录有523人被处决，其中459人被步枪射杀，20人被绞死（13人因犯逃兵罪），其余44人被炮决。在这44人中，有4人犯逃兵罪，而不是叛变。<ref>''Parliament of Great Britain'' (1859), [https://books.google.com/books?id=Tq5bAAAAQAAJ&pg=RA1-PA80 p. 80] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Tq5bAAAAQAAJ&pg=RA1-PA80 |date=20201103051259 }}</ref>阿格拉（Agra）地区在7月到11月的官方统计数据显示，在被判死刑的78人中，2人被减刑为监禁，4人被炮决决。<ref>''Indian News'' (1858), [https://books.google.com/books?id=43lNAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA125 p. 125] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=43lNAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA125 |date=20201023175624 }}</ref>来自[[印多尔|印多尔]]的官方统计数据表明，在官方处罚的393名印度兵中，有32人被处决，其中21人被炮决。<ref>''Shrivastav'' (1971), [https://books.google.com/books?id=hqE8AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA108 p. 108] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hqE8AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA108 |date=20200731121906 }}</ref>

上述案例是军事法庭正式审判后执行死刑的例子，因此没有记录在战斗中、非正式处决或屠杀期间发生的案例。

一些英国人确信叛乱的印度兵曾将英国妇女炮决。<ref>See, for example, remark by colonel Mylne, ''Russell'' (1859), [https://books.google.com/books?id=Mk0QAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA45 p. 45] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Mk0QAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA45 |date=20200831192718 }}</ref>一些消息人士提到的一个具体案例涉及到伯奇（Birch）夫妇、埃克福德（Eckford）夫人和德方丹（Defontaine）夫人。据说他们都是在[[法泰赫加尔|法泰赫加尔]]被炮决的。<ref>In a letter dated 30 August 1857, received by [[William_Muir|William Muir]] working as an intelligence officer, the persons were Mr. Bridges (an indigo planter), his wife, his mother-in-law and their daughter Mrs. Eckford. ''Muir, Coldstream'' (1902), [https://archive.org/stream/recordsintellig00indigoog#page/n510/mode/2up p. 501].</ref><ref>[http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article66008933 The Inquirer & Commercial News, Wednesday 7 April 1858], [http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&d=LT18571212.2.15&l=mi&e=-------10--1----0-- "Phoenix", 10 September 1857] {{Wayback|url=http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&d=LT18571212.2.15&l=mi&e=-------10--1----0-- |date=20160310063536 }}, ''Noel'' (1859), [https://books.google.com/books?id=O3gOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA461 p. 461] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O3gOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA461 |date=20200801144352 }}</ref>

一个被炮决的印度士兵头骨在英国的一个酒吧里被发现，这也成了一本书——《阿鲁姆·比格的头骨：1857年一位反叛者的生与死》（The Skull of Alum Bheg: The Life and Death of a Rebel of 1857）的主题。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-43616597 |title=What a skull in an English pub says about India's 1857 mutiny, ''BBC News'', Thursday 5 April 2018 |access-date=2020-10-22 |archive-date=2020-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129203732/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-43616597 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 

=== 1857年之后 ===
[[印度民族起义|印度民族起义]]中并不是英国军队最后一次使用大炮来执行死刑。例如在1871年，65名锡克教徒被军队炮决。<ref>In this case, however, the [[viceroy_of_India|viceroy of India]], [[Richard_Bourke,_6th_Earl_of_Mayo|Richard Bourke]], earl of Mayo, disowned the action of Mr. Cowan, who presided over the first 49 executions and dismissed that officer responsible for the mass execution. ''Knight'' (2012), [https://books.google.com/books?id=NVfTufIqlD8C&pg=PA13 p. 13] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NVfTufIqlD8C&pg=PA13 |date=20200813122821 }}. However, this was on basis of a procedural point concerning how the trial under Cowan had been held; Mr. Forsyth, Mr. Cowan's hierarchical superior, also blew the last 16 from guns, some time thereafter, but according to requirements of "fair trial". ''Singh'' (1995), [https://books.google.com/books?id=2lu7HatPQCoC&pg=PA503 p. 503–507] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2lu7HatPQCoC&pg=PA503 |date=20201030043427 }}.</ref>

== 阿富汗 ==
从19世纪早期到1930年，在[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]使用炮决执行死刑的传统得到了证实。以下是一些例子：

=== 早期案例 ===
1802年，{{Le|马赫米德·沙阿·杜兰尼|Mahmud Shah Durrani}}的军队对[[吉尔吉人|吉尔吉人]]部落造成了惨重的打击，为了阻止进一步的挑衅，他下令将一位领导人和他的两个儿子炮决，并用吉尔吉人的头骨建造了一座[[叫拜樓|宣礼塔]]。<ref>''Noelle'' (2012), [https://books.google.com/books?id=ylTi-e2C_0IC&pg=PP290 p. 290] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ylTi-e2C_0IC&pg=PP290 |date=20200719061701 }}</ref>1803年，当{{Le|沙阿·舒亚·杜兰尼|Shah Shujah Durrani}}将他同父异母的兄弟马赫穆德（Mahmud）赶下台后，他报复了马赫穆德的一个盟友阿希克（Ashik），将他炮决，因为他背叛了舒亚和马赫穆德的同父异母兄弟{{Le|扎曼·沙阿·杜兰尼|Zaman Shah Durrani}}，扎曼·沙阿·杜兰尼在1800年被马赫穆德赶下台之前是[[杜兰尼帝国|杜兰尼帝国]]的国王。<ref>''Tate'' (1911), on treachery, [https://archive.org/stream/kingdomofafghani00taterich#page/114/mode/2up p. 115], on blowing from a gun, [https://archive.org/stream/kingdomofafghani00taterich#page/120/mode/2up p. 121].</ref>

=== 铁人埃米尔，1880-1901 ===
1880年，[[阿布杜爾·拉赫曼汗|阿布杜尔·拉赫曼汗]]成为阿富汗的[[埃米尔|埃米尔]]，他很快就因为他的残暴和强硬统治而获得了“铁人埃米尔”（the iron emir）的绰号。有消息估计，在他执政的20年间，平均每年有5000人被处决，其中一些人被炮决。<ref>Apart from blowing from guns, the source mention as well that people could be bayoneted to death, hanged, crucified, disemboweled, sawn in two, hanged or dragged to death behind horses. ''Akbarzadeh, Macqueen'' (2008), [https://books.google.com/books?id=hEGj-55dCvkC&pg=PA93 p. 93] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hEGj-55dCvkC&pg=PA93 |date=20200727163906 }}. [[Lord_Curzon|Lord Curzon]], visiting Kabul in 1894, narrates the following chilling story about a rapist: "One official who had outraged a woman was stripped naked and placed in a hole dug for the purpose on the top of a high hill outside Kabul. It was in mid-winter; and water was then poured upon him until he was converted into an icicle and frozen alive. As the Amir sardonically remarked, “He would never be too hot again.”" ''Edwards'' (1996), [https://books.google.com/books?id=IncGaivUHu8C&pg=PA111 p. 111] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IncGaivUHu8C&pg=PA111 |date=20201105092042 }}.</ref>例如，仅在1889年12月就有24人被记录炮决，还有许多人被以其它方式处决。<ref>''Lee'' (1996), [https://books.google.com/books?id=nYaamE_3kD4C&pg=PA551 p. 551] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nYaamE_3kD4C&pg=PA551 |date=20200831055116 }}. In 1891 Herat, a rebel leader was also blown from a gun, [https://books.google.com/books?id=nYaamE_3kD4C&pg=PA580 p. 580] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nYaamE_3kD4C&pg=PA580 |date=20201103095430 }}.</ref>

=== 塔吉克人恐怖统治时期，1929年 ===
1929年1月，当塔吉克人{{Le|哈比布拉·卡拉卡尼|Habibullāh Kalakāni}}成为[[埃米尔|埃米尔]]后，阿富汗爆发了新一轮极端暴力事件。英国大臣汉弗莱斯（Humphreys）写道：“没有什么是安全的，房屋被肆意掠夺，妇女被蹂躏，这样的恐怖统治在血腥的阿富汗历史中是前所未有的。”政治对手经常被炮决或以其他方式处决。<ref>Letter from Humphreys to the foreign secretary from 20 January 1929, cited in ''Roberts'' (2003), [https://books.google.com/books?id=Pj8DIT_bva0C&pg=PA51 p. 51] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Pj8DIT_bva0C&pg=PA51 |date=20201105204308 }} and [https://books.google.com/books?id=Pj8DIT_bva0C&pg=PA61 p. 61] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Pj8DIT_bva0C&pg=PA61 |date=20200808142440 }}. For the case of Ali Ahmad Khan blown by guns in July 1929, see ''Lee'' (1996), [https://books.google.com/books?id=nYaamE_3kD4C&pg=PA378 p. 378] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nYaamE_3kD4C&pg=PA378 |date=20201105155751 }}.</ref>哈比布拉的政权在1929年10月被推翻，之后库赫斯塔尼（Kuhestani）塔吉克人遭到迫害。1930年4月6日《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》的一篇文章的标题是：“11名阿富汗人在[[喀布尔|喀布尔]]被炮决”。<ref name="auto2">''Cullather, Meyerowitz'' (2003), [https://books.google.com/books?id=V5NdS-k7FUMC&pg=PA50 p. 50]</ref>


== 小说中的炮决 ==
在{{Le|乔治·麦克唐纳·弗莱泽|George MacDonald Fraser}}以[[印度民族起义|印度民族起义]]为背景的小说《Flashman in the Great Game》中，一个冒充印度人的英国军官哈里·弗莱西曼（Harry Flashman）在英国人对[[詹西王后|詹西王后]]营地的袭击中昏了过去并被俘虏。弗莱西曼被当作反叛分子，醒来时发现被塞住嘴绑在大炮口上。他勉强逃过了死刑，并释放了要和他一起被处决的叛乱分子。对于一个通常被描绘成说谎者、恶霸和无赖的角色来说，这是一种不同寻常的人道行为。

《[[蒸汽屋|蒸汽屋]]》是[[儒勒·凡尔纳|儒勒·凡尔纳]]1880年的一部小说，以那纳·萨伊布（Nana Sahib）被大炮炸死结尾。

在{{Le|亨利·毕姆·派珀|H. Beam Piper}}的科幻小说《Lord Kalvan of Otherwhen》中，主角卡尔文（Kalvan）从我们的宇宙时空转移到了[[架空历史|架空历史]]，他提出应该用炮决杀死堕落的“教会”斯蒂芬会馆（Styphon's House）的神职人员。他对自己辩解说英国人曾对反叛的印度兵使用这种手段，“在开明的[[维多利亚女王|维多利亚女王]]统治时期，你还能得到比那更多的[[维多利亚时代道德观念|尊敬]]吗？”卡尔文还认为这构成了“一个糟糕的关于‘炮’制殉道圣人的[[双关语|双关语]]”。这么说特别合适，因为“斯蒂芬会馆”将它的的财富作为火药的唯一来源。

